@@TJvMRUManager.StartEllipsis
Summary
  Specifies how to shorten a path when it is too long.
Description
  Use StartEllipsis to specify where any ellipsis characters should appear in a path string that
  needs shortening.
  
  If StartEllipsis is true, the path is cut at the start, leaving the trailing part alone. If it is
  false, the path is cut approximately in the middle.
  
  Note that if MaxLength is 0, no cutting of the path is performed and StartEllipsis has no relevance.

