@@TJvMRUManager.RecentMenu
Summary
  Specifies the menu item to use as an anchor for the MRU list.
Description
  Assign an existing menu item either in a main menu or popup menu to RecentMenu to enable the MRU
  list to be displayed. Depending on the value of MenuLocation, the MRU list either appears on the
  same level as RecentMenu or as a child menu of RecentMenu.
  
  If you don't assign a menu item to RecentMenu, no MRU items will be shown. You can still use the
  MRU manager in an invisible mode.

