@@TJvMRUManager.Capacity
Summary
  Specifies how many items can be in the list.
Description
  Use Capacity to specify how many items the list can hold. When a new item is added that would make
  the list exceed Capacity, the oldest item is removed. What item is considered the "oldest item" is
  determined by the settings of Mode.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvMRUManager.AutoUpdate
Summary
  Specifies whether the state of the menu is updated automatically or not.
Description
  When AutoUpdate is true, changing properties of the component that affects the menu, automatically
  updates and rebuilds the menu as necessary.
  
  If you are doing lengthy updates or several changes at once, set AutoUpdate to false to avoid
  unnecessary recalculations and updates. When you are finished set AutoUpdate to true again.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvMRUManager.AutoEnable
Summary
  Specifies whether the menu's Enabled state should change automatically.
Description
  Use AutoEnable to control whether RecentMenu is enabled/disabled automatically when items are added
  and removed. If true, RecentMenu is disabled as long as there are no items in the list. If false,
  RecentMenu.Enabled will not be changed by the MRU manager.

